snapshot:
ENCODING STRATEGY — flat typed arrays for hot fields, sparse records for event/rare fields:

```ts
// host emits this shape each tick via client.updateSharedState(patch)
type SnapshotPatch = {
  // Hot: changes every tick for moving units.
  // 80 units × 5 × 2 bytes = 800 bytes as Int16Array, base64 ~1100 bytes.
  // Encoded as base64 string of Int16Array: [x0,y0,vx0,vy0,hp0, x1,y1,...] 
  unitPositions?: string;  // base64(Int16Array[unitCount*5])

  // Warm: changes when combat events happen — sparse record, only dirty units
  unitHp?: Record<string, number>;  // unitId → current hp (0-maxHp)

  // Cold: changes rarely (level up, gold, item buy)
  heroStats?: Record<string, HeroStats>;
  heroGold?: Record<string, number>;
  towerHp?: Record<string, number>;    // towerId → hp
  towerDead?: Record<string, true>;

  // Events: one-shot, cleared next tick
  deaths?: string[];          // unitId array
  spawnedCreeps?: SpawnedCreep[];
  projectiles?: Record<string, ProjectileState>; // born or moved
  projectilesRemoved?: string[];

  // Game phase
  gameTime?: number;          // seconds since match start
  winner?: "radiant"|"dire"|null;
};
```

UNIT POSITION ENCODING:
```ts
// Host side — build flat Int16Array per tick
function encodePositions(units: UnitSim[]): string {
  const buf = new Int16Array(units.length * 5);
  for (let i = 0; i < units.length; i++) {
    const u = units[i]!;
    buf[i*5+0] = Math.round(u.x);          // world px, fits in Int16 for 32768px map
    buf[i*5+1] = Math.round(u.y);
    buf[i*5+2] = Math.round(u.vx * 10);    // velocity ×10 for sub-px precision
    buf[i*5+3] = Math.round(u.vy * 10);
    buf[i*5+4] = u.hp;                     // 0-32767
  }
  return btoa(String.fromCharCode(...new Uint8Array(buf.buffer)));
}
// Client side — decode and lerp display positions
function decodePositions(b64: string, units: ClientUnit[]): void {
  const bytes = Uint8Array.from(atob(b64), c => c.charCodeAt(0));
  const buf = new Int16Array(bytes.buffer);
  for (let i = 0; i < units.length; i++) {
    units[i]!.targetX = buf[i*5+0];
    units[i]!.targetY = buf[i*5+1];
    // vx/vy used for client-side extrapolation between snapshots
    units[i]!.targetVx = buf[i*5+2] / 10;
    units[i]!.targetVy = buf[i*5+3] / 10;
  }
}
```

SIZE ESTIMATE at 80 units, 15Hz:
- unitPositions: 80×5×2 bytes = 800 bytes → base64 ~1100 bytes
- unitHp (only dirty): ~0-20 units × 10 bytes = 200 bytes
- projectiles: ~10 × 50 bytes = 500 bytes
- Other cold fields: ~200 bytes
- Total per tick: ~2KB typical, ~4KB spike — well within WebSocket budget.

CLIENT INTERPOLATION:
```ts
// In client update() every frame (60fps)
function interpolateUnit(u: ClientUnit, delta: number): void {
  const LERP = 1 - Math.pow(0.01, delta / 1000); // ~10x speed factor
  u.displayX = Phaser.Math.Linear(u.displayX, u.targetX, LERP * 10);
  u.displayY = Phaser.Math.Linear(u.displayY, u.targetY, LERP * 10);
  // Extrapolate between snapshots using last known velocity:
  u.targetX += u.targetVx * delta;
  u.targetY += u.targetVy * delta;
  u.container.setPosition(u.displayX, u.displayY);
  u.container.setDepth(u.displayY);  // re-sort every frame
}
```

